recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 2 large (3.5oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 2 slice(s) (2.3oz)
  • Avocado, 4 tbsp(s) (2.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Fruit, any type, 1 small piece(s) (3.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Add water to a large saucepan until 3 inches deep. Bring to a boil and then reduce to a gentle simmer. Crack one egg into a small bowl. Using a large spoon, gently stir the water in a circular motion to create a whirlpool. Carefully slide the egg into the water. Immediately repeat with the second egg.

Allow the eggs to poach for about 3 to 4 minutes for runny yolks and 4 to 5 minutes for firmer yolks. Remove eggs with a slotted spoon once cooked to your liking.

In the meantime, toast the bread and spread both slices with avocado. Top with poached eggs. Season to taste.

Follow with piece of fresh fruit, or save for a mid-morning snack.

recipieName: Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • White onion, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.7oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Thyme, fresh, 2 tsp(s), 5 sprigs (0.1oz)
  • Eggplant, ¼ eggplant(s), unpeeled, chopped (4.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.7oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 medium, diced (6.9oz)
  • Tomatoes, canned, 1 can(s) (6.7oz)
  • Lentils, canned, drained, 1 cup(s), rinsed (6.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Portabella mushrooms, 2 piece(s), whole (5.9oz)
  • Arugula, 4 cup(s) (2.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables instructions

Preheat oven 400°F. Lightly grease a medium roasting pan.

Heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, cook stirring for 3 minutes until soft. Stir in the thyme, eggplant, bell pepper and zucchini. Cook stirring for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and 1/3 cup of water. Bring to a simmer. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until ratatouille thickens slightly. Remove from the heat, stir in the lentils. Season to taste. Spoon into the roasting pan.

Nestle the mushrooms in the ratatouille. Roast for 15 minutes until mushrooms are just tender. Divide into two portions. Spoon remaining 2 teaspoons of oil over the arugula, toss to coat. Scatter the arugula over the mushrooms. Season to taste. Serve.

TIP: If you prefer, you can swap the lentils for 2 poached eggs and serve them on top of the mushrooms and ratatouille.

recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 1 large, raw (1.8oz)
  • Light mayo, 1 tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, 1½ tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Cumin, ground, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), ground
  • Lemon, ¼ medium, juiced (0.7oz)
  • Whole-wheat bread, 2 slice(s) (2.3oz)
  • Carrot, shredded, ¼ cup(s) (1oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, 5 cherry tomato(es), diced (3oz)
  • Baby spinach, 1 handful(s) (0.8oz)
  • Vegetable sticks (carrot, celery, cucumber, bell pepper), 1 cup(s) (4oz)
  • Fruit, any type, 1 small piece(s) (3.5oz)

recipeInstructions:
Place egg in a small saucepan, covering with cold water and bringing to the boil over high heat. Once boiling, immediately reduce heat to medium and gently boil for 8 minutes. Remove from hot water and place in ice cold water until cool.

Remove egg from water, discard shell and mash egg together with mayo, onion, cumin, black pepper, and lemon juice.

Spread one slice of bread with curried egg mixture and top with carrot, tomatoes and spinach. Top with other slice to make a sandwich. Serve with a side of vegetable sticks.

Enjoy a piece of fruit & yogurt for dessert.

TIP: For cooler days, toast sandwich in a sandwich press for a warm lunch option. If preferred, add salad vegetables after toasting. Cook eggs at the start of the week and store in the fridge for use in lunch meals and snacks. Boiled eggs can be kept for up to one week in the fridge, with their shells left on.

recipeIngredients:
• Chicken breast, raw, 6 oz(s) (6oz)
  • Sweet chili sauce, low-sodium, 1 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Baby bok choy, 1 bunch(es) (4.2oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Green beans, trimmed, 1 cup(s), chopped (3.5oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ½ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Basil, fresh, ½ cup(s), whole leaves, Thai or sweet basil (0.4oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Sweet chili chicken & basil stir-fry according to recipe instructions below. Enjoy one serving for dinner.

Refrigerate the remaining serving in an airtight container for later in the week. Keep the sesame seeds and basil in separate containers and only add once ready to eat.

Sweet chili chicken & basil stir-fry instructions

Thinly slice the chicken, place into a bowl. Spoon over half the sweet chili sauce, stir to coat.

Chop the bok choy leaves and place onto a plate. Thinly slice the bok choy base.

Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a wok over high heat. Add the chicken, stir-fry 1 minute until golden, remove to a plate. Reduce heat to medium-high. Add the onion and 1 tablespoon water, stir-fry for 30 seconds, until soft. Add the remaining 1 teaspoon oil, green beans and bok choy base and stir-fry, stirring to coat in the oil and combine the vegetables. Add another 2 teaspoons water, cover the wok and wait 30 seconds.

Remove the lid, add the bell pepper and return the chicken. Add the remaining sweet chili sauce, stir-fry for 1 minute until chicken is warmed through. Stir through the chopped bok choy leaves. Remove from heat.

Just before serving, add the basil and sesame seeds, stir to combine. Divide between two serving bowls and serve.

TIP: You can replace the sweet chili sauce with chili jam stir-fry paste, which is available in the Asian sauce section at the supermarket.

recipeIngredients:
• Zucchini, noodles, 3½ cup(s) (11.3oz)
  • Ground pork, lean, raw, 6 oz(s) (6oz)
  • Eggs, 1 large, raw (1.8oz)
  • Paprika, 1 tsp(s), dried, smoked (0.1oz)
  • Cumin, ground, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Dried mixed herbs, 2 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Parsley, fresh, 2 tbsp(s), finely chopped (0.3oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Tomatoes, canned, 14½ oz(s), 1 small can (14.5oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), ground, to taste
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Pork meatballs on zoodles according to recipe instructions.

Serve one portion of the recipe for dinner tonight and transfer second portion to an airtight container and refrigerate for use later in the week.

Pork meatballs on zoodles instructions

Preheat the oven to 350°F.

Bring a small pot of water to the boil, and cook the zoodles for 1 to 2 minutes until soft. Strain, and leave to one side.

Combine the ground pork in a bowl with egg, paprika, cumin, half the dried mixed herbs and half of the fresh parsley. Shape into balls and place on a baking tray lined with parchment paper or foil. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cooked through. Remove from the oven and place to one side.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and saute for 2 to 3 minutes or until transparent. Add tomatoes in to the pan and reduce the heat. Then add the remaining dried mixed herbs and fresh parsley, stir together, and bring to the simmer. Add the meatballs to the sauce, and continue to cook until sauce is reduced.

Divide the zoodles between two serving bowls, add the meatballs and sauce over the top, and sprinkle with black pepper.
